Former Vice President of Nigeria, Atiku Abubakar, has expressed gratitude to God over the recovery of his son, Mohammed, from the deadly coronavirus. DAILY POST had reported that Mohammed announced his recovery from COVID-19 on Monday after several weeks in isolation centre. Mohammed was discharged on Monday after testing negative twice for coronavirus. Reacting, Atiku on Twitter wrote, “With gratitude to God, we are excited, @Mo_Atiku. It couldn’t have come at a better time of the Ramadan. “I thank you all for your prayers, even as we remain indebted to the medical personnel who have stayed tireless in their efforts.”